We ordered food from Pupuseria Ana/Elizabeth via doordash. When the driver got here we only received one out of the 4 items that we ordered. We called the restaurant to let them know about the food we were missing, and talked to two people about it before we got hung up on. We thought it was an accident and tried to call back, but no one would answer, so we called off another phone thinking that maybe it wasn't an accident and they hung up on us on purpose. When we called off another phone and they immediately picked up,  and we tried to explain our issue and immediately were cut off and told they don't speak English and they hung up on us AGAIN! We were very excited to try this place since they got such great reviews, but the customer service was absolutely horrible and we will never order from them again.  Thankfully we were able to dispute it on doordash as well to let them know what we were missing and they refunded our money immediately.  Again, this was our first experience, and the customer service was horrible to say the least.

Food was extremely salty. We got the steak dinner, soup, and pupusas. One bite into the steak and you could taste the extreme amount of salt, the water in the soup was basically salt water, and the pupusas made you cringe. The rice and beans were ok. The store bought coconut water was the best tasting thing there. I spoke to the cook about the taste of the food  and all I was told was that they couldn't do anything about it because I had touched the food. Of course I touched it, how else were I to taste the extreme amount of salt. I do not recommend this place at all. They were rude in answering me when my spoke calmly to them not looking for much in return as this looks like a small family business. A simple "sorry" would have sufficed however rudeness was mode of currency.
